Setting up aliases for common commands:
ls -la ~
// .gitconfig
// One way: edit the .gitconfig file
// 2nd way: use the global config command as follows:
syntax:
git config --global alias.<shortcuts> <git_command>
Example:
git config --global alias.st "status"
// if the command comprise space in it, we need to provide double quote.
cat .gitconfig

Some common shortcuts:
git config --global alias.co checkout
git config --global alias.ci commit
git config --global alias.br branch
git config --global alias..df diff
git config --global alias.dfg "diff --staged"
git config --global alias.dfc "diff --cached"
git config --global alias.logg "log --graph --decorate --oneline --abbrev-commit --all"
